HEADWORD: Athecata
<hw>Ath`e*ca"ta</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ chest, box.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of Hydroidea in which the zooids are naked, or not
inclosed in a capsule. See <er>Tubularian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atheism</ent>⟦br⟧
